                            <comment id="13295221" author="dependablejoe" created="Thu, 14 Jun 2012 18:40:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Example code of problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13693125" author="horstr" created="Tue, 25 Jun 2013 15:27:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is particularly troublesome for accessibility because screen readers cannot access pages beyond the first document.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is this a fundamental issue requiring major changes or can this be fixed by merely linking the tag information of individual documents?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13705839" author="gerhardt" created="Thu, 11 Jul 2013 13:54:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch against 1.8.2 implements merging tag information if both source and destination are tagged.&lt;br/&gt;
Tag information will be removed if one document isn&apos;t tagged.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please review and apply.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13806339" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 27 Oct 2013 14:18:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I applied the changes in revision 1536136 as proposed. I also extended XObjectForms/XObjectImages to be part of a structural parent tree.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TODO: the XObjects are not updated when merging tagged pdfs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the contribution!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
